# GOVERNMENT SCHEMES NAVIGATOR
## Requirements & Technical Design Document

---

# PART 1: REQUIREMENTS SPECIFICATION

## 1. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS

### 1.1 User Stories & Core Flows

#### User Story 1: Farmer Checking Eligibility
```
AS A farmer earning â‚¹2.5 lakh/year with 1.5 hectares of land
I WANT TO discover government benefits I qualify for
SO THAT I can access financial support without spending hours in offices

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
âœ“ User sends WhatsApp message: "farmer, earning 2.5 lakh, 1.5 hectare"
âœ“ System responds in <10 seconds with eligible schemes in Hindi
âœ“ Response includes: Scheme name, benefit amount, eligibility status, next steps
âœ“ User can ask follow-up questions (e.g., "how to apply for PM Kisan?")
```

#### User Story 2: Mother Checking Health Benefits
```
AS A mother with 2 children earning â‚¹1.8 lakh/year
I WANT TO understand what healthcare coverage I'm entitled to
SO THAT I don't go into debt during medical emergencies

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
âœ“ User calls IVR number, selects "Check health benefits"
âœ“ System asks: Aadhar (voice input) â†’ Family income â†’ Number of dependents
âœ“ Returns: Ayushman Bharat (â‚¹5L) + state health schemes + nutrition benefits
âœ“ Provides: List of hospitals, how to register, what docs needed
âœ“ Sends SMS confirmation with enrollment center details
```

#### User Story 3: Senior Citizen Accessing Pension Info
```
AS A retired person, age 65
I WANT TO know if I qualify for government pensions/schemes
SO THAT I have stable income in old age

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
âœ“ User receives SMS: "Reply with your age and monthly income to check benefits"
âœ“ User replies: "65, income 8000"
âœ“ System sends back: Eligible schemes (name, monthly amount, how to apply)
âœ“ User can request: "Send nearest enrollment center" via SMS
âœ“ System sends address + contact details of nearest center
```

### 1.2 Schemes Covered (Phase 1)

#### Scheme Matrix: Eligibility Criteria

| Scheme | Category | Annual Income Limit | Location | Key Docs | Benefit |
|--------|----------|-------------------|----------|----------|---------|
| **PM Kisan** | Farmers | Unlimited (<2 hectares land) | All states | Land deed, Aadhar, Bank | â‚¹6,000/year |
| **Ayushman Bharat (PM-JAY)** | Low-income families | <â‚¹5 lakh (SECC) | All states | Aadhar, household proof | â‚¹5 lakh health insurance/year |
| **PM Awas Yojana** | Housing | <â‚¹6 lakh (EWS), <â‚¹12 lakh (LIG) | All states | Income proof, ID, property | â‚¹2.67 lakh subsidy |
| **UP Housing Scheme** | State-specific | <â‚¹8 lakh | UP only | Aadhar, land doc, income | â‚¹2.5 lakh subsidy |
| **Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima** | Farmers | All | Agricultural areas | Land deed, crop type | Crop insurance (premium subsidy) |
| **PMJDY** | Unbanked, unemployed | All | All states | ID, address, photo | Free bank account + insurance |
| **Pension Schemes** | Senior citizens, disabled | <â‚¹2 lakh | All states | Age proof, ID | â‚¹500-5,000/month |
| **Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana** | Girl child | All (for daughters) | All states | Birth cert, parent ID | 8.2% annual returns |
| **Maternity Benefit (JSY)** | Pregnant women | All | All states | Medical card, ID | â‚¹1,400-â‚¹6,000 + free delivery |
| **Scholarship Programs** | Students | Family income <â‚¹2.5L | All states | School ID, income proof | â‚¹5,000-â‚¹50,000/year |

